answerText: The Unnamable [or L'innommable][10] Molloy, Malone Dies and The Unnamable are the volumes of a trilogy by this author, who also wrote a play in which "nothing happens, twice," Waiting for Godot.

subject: Literature
question: Question: This novel, the third in a trilogy, ends with the words "You must go on, I can't go on, I'll go on." For 10 points each: [10] Name this 1953 novel which consists of the ruminations of an immobile character. Other characters in this novel are named Mahood and Worm.
